## **üöÄ Welcome to the Vercel Workshop\!**

Whether you're a complete beginner or have some experience, this workshop is designed to help you grasp the basics of **GitHub** and learn how to **deploy your project using Vercel**. By the end of this session, you'll know how to make your projects accessible to anyone, anywhere, with a simple link\!

## **üéØ Objectives:**

* Use GitHub to store and manage your projects.  
* Clone, commit, push, and pull repositories using GitHub Desktop.  
* Deploy your project using Vercel and make it live on the web.

---

## **üìÅ Basics of Git & GitHub**

### **What is GitHub?**

GitHub is a platform that allows developers to **store**, **manage**, and **collaborate** on code using **Git**. It serves as a cloud-based repository for your projects.

### **Key GitHub Terminologies:**

* **Folder** ‚Üí **Repository**  
* **Changes** ‚Üí **Commit**

### **Prerequisites for the Workshop:**

* Install **GitHub Desktop** on your laptop/PC ‚Üí [Download Here](https://desktop.github.com/)  
* Create an account on **GitHub** ‚Üí [Sign Up Here](https://github.com/)

---

## **üíª GitHub Desktop ‚Äî Quick Guide**

### **1Ô∏è‚É£ Cloning a Repository:**

1. Open **GitHub Desktop**.  
2. Click **File \> Clone Repository**.  
3. Select the repository or paste the URL.  
4. Choose a local path and click **Clone**.

### **2Ô∏è‚É£ Creating a New Repository:**

1. In GitHub Desktop, click **File \> New Repository**.  
2. Add repository name, description, and local path.  
3. Initialize with a **README** if needed.  
4. Click **Create Repository**.

### **3Ô∏è‚É£ Making Changes and Committing:**

1. Modify files in your local directory.  
2. Open **GitHub Desktop** ‚Äî changed files will be listed.  
3. Write a **commit message**.  
4. Click **Commit to main**.

### **4Ô∏è‚É£ Pushing Changes to GitHub:**

1. After committing, click **Push origin** to upload changes to GitHub.

### **5Ô∏è‚É£ Pulling Changes from GitHub:**

1. Click **Fetch origin** to check for updates.  
2. Click **Pull origin** to sync changes.

## **üåê Workshop II: Deploying Your Project Using Vercel**

### **1Ô∏è‚É£ Creating a Vercel Account:**

1. Visit [vercel.com](https://vercel.com/).  
2. Click **Sign Up**.  
3. Choose **GitHub**, **GitLab**, or **Bitbucket** to sign in.  
4. Authorize Vercel to access your repositories.  
5. Complete the setup by selecting your preferred settings.

### **2Ô∏è‚É£ Deploying with Vercel Dashboard:**

1. Go to the **Vercel Dashboard** ‚Üí [vercel.com/dashboard](https://vercel.com/dashboard).  
2. Click **New Project**.  
3. Select the **GitHub repository** you want to deploy (**ensure the repo is public**).  
4. Configure build settings if needed (Vercel usually auto-detects the framework).  
5. Click **Deploy**.

---

## **üí° Tips for a Smooth Deployment:**

* **Make sure your repository is public** for seamless deployment.  
* **Use a `README.md`** to make your repository more understandable.
